DOMMatrixMultiplySelf.summary: The multiplySelf() method of the interface multiplies a matrix by the otherMatrix parameter, computing the dot product of the original matrix and the specified matrix: Aâ‹…B. If no matrix is specified as the multiplier, the matrix is multiplied by a matrix in which every element is 0 except the bottom-right corner and the element immediately above and to its left: m33 and m34. These have the default value of 1.

remarks.para: To multiply a matrix without mutating it, see .

DOMMatrixMultiplySelf.returns: Returns itself; the DOMMatrix updated to the results of the applied multiplications.
